<p>At 366 feet tall and 516 feet wide, this massive structure on the Las Vegas Strip stands out due to its truly impressive engineering. The Sphere’s outside shell is covered in 1.2 million LED lights that allow the building to take on any appearance, including a giant emoji. Inside, the sound system is the largest of its type, and the venue can create wind, seat vibrations, and even scents for the audience to enjoy. The screen inside is also so massive that it requires a new camera system just to capture 18K footage to fill it. It’s an unreal experience, and it still has a ton of potential as creators push the limits of what it can do.</p>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center" id="home" style="font-style:normal;font-weight:700">Home</h2>



<p>Innovation doesn’t always start with an enormous change from what came before. Sometimes, it’s the small adjustments that have outsized effects well beyond their own industries. Sure, the list includes a 50-pound solid-state battery power station—a type of tech that’s been notoriously difficult to scale—but there’s also a small spring in a shock-absorbing hammer, and a little lever in an easy-to-install power outlet. These sometimes seemingly iterative changes can ripple and we expect to see the effects of this year’s winners for a long time coming.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-grand-award-winner-home">Grand Award Winner, Home</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-solid-state-technology-by-yoshino-the-first-portable-power-stations-to-use-solid-state-batteries">Solid-state technology by Yoshino: The first portable power stations to use solid-state batteries</h3>


<div
    class="ProductCardSimple"
  data-id="ProductCardSimple"
>
  <div class="ProductCardSimple-image">
                          <a target="_blank" href="https://yoshinopower.com/" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener noreferrer">
                    <figure class="wp-block-image size-large">
            <img decoding="async" src="https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2023/11/29/Yoshino-Power-B4000SST-FNL.jpg?auto=webp&amp;width=800&amp;crop=16:10,offset-x50" srcset="https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2023/11/29/Yoshino-Power-B4000SST-FNL.jpg?auto=webp&optimize=high&width=330&crop=16:10,offset-x50 330w,https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2023/11/29/Yoshino-Power-B4000SST-FNL.jpg?auto=webp&optimize=high&width=360&crop=16:10,offset-x50 360w,https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2023/11/29/Yoshino-Power-B4000SST-FNL.jpg?auto=webp&optimize=high&width=382&crop=16:10,offset-x50 382w,https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2023/11/29/Yoshino-Power-B4000SST-FNL.jpg?auto=webp&optimize=high&width=800&crop=16:10,offset-x50 800w,https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2023/11/29/Yoshino-Power-B4000SST-FNL.jpg?auto=webp&optimize=high&width=1440&crop=16:10,offset-x50 1440w" data-image="https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2023/11/29/Yoshino-Power-B4000SST-FNL.jpg?auto=webp&amp;width=800&amp;crop=16:10,offset-x50" loading="lazy" width="800" height="500" alt="Best of What's New photo">
                      </figure>
                  </a>
            </div>
  <div class="ProductCardSimple-content">
          <figcaption class="ProductCardSimple-contentDescription">
        <p><em>Yoshino</em></p>

      </figcaption>
              <p class="ProductCardSimple-contentBtnWrap">
        <a class="ProductCardSimple-contentBtn btn" href="https://yoshinopower.com/"
         target="_blank" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener noreferrer">Learn More</a>
      </p>
      </div>
</div>



<p>Type “solid-state batteries” into Google and you’ll see a list of frequently asked questions along the lines of, “Are solid-state batteries coming?” Well, if you need a portable power station capable of providing 330 to 4,000 watts of juice, they’re already here. Solid-state batteries promise to provide longer-lasting, more powerful replacements for lithium-ion batteries, but the cost has made them impractical for most usages, especially in larger sizes. Yoshino has found a way to scale solid-state cells into portable power stations that weigh anywhere from 10 to 54 pounds. They’re the first devices of their size to run on solid-state batteries. What’s more, is you won’t have to worry about damage causing a dangerous fire. Unlike liquid electrolyte-based lithium-ion batteries, which can explode in flame when punctured, solid-state batteries are, well, solid and much more rugged.&nbsp;</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-decora-edge-outlets-and-switches-by-leviton-the-easiest-diy-power-outlet-installation-ever">Decora Edge outlets and switches by Leviton: The easiest DIY power outlet installation ever</h3>


